RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 1 1 1/16M Turf CR: 79. Claiming Purse 40400. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $20,000, allowed 4 lbs. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race on the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEYOND THE PALE , reluctant to load into the starting gate, raced in contention down the backstretch, swung out in upper stretch, took command near the sixteenth pole and drove clear. MOSLEY NATURAL opened up mid way down the backstretch, remained clear and well off the rail in upper stretch and tired in the drive. BALLYHOO PRINCE bore out leaving the starting gate, raced inside horses through out and failed to rally. MASTER OF NONE , never far back, moved up in the three path turning for home and failed to rally in an even effort. SOROLLA bumped with PURSUING PACE leaving the starting gate, circled the far turn four wide and was no factor. PURSUING PACE bumped with SOROLLA when forced out by BALLYHOO PRINCE leaving the starting gate, was rank behind horses approaching the first turn, swung to the six path in upper stretch and passed tired rivals. BUNKER HILL raced in mid pack and was not a threat. ALOTTACENTS , a forward factor along the inner rail, chased the pace to the stretch and faltered. FOOD FOODIE , along the inner rail much of the race, gave way. NOBLE PRENDERGAST , four wide the first turn, was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 86. Claiming Purse 23540. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 30 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000, if for $6,000, allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIALING DIXIE , hustled from the gate, disputed the pace to the inside of SEANOW and BACKATYA, gained a slim lead heading to the eighth pole, spurted clear under a drive soon after, kept on under solid pressure and had enough left to hold sway. SEANOW set a pressured pace between rivals, emerged in a duel to the outside of the winner in upper stretch, saw that one get away a bit leaving the furlong grounds, battled back gamely through the final seventy yards but had his run fall just short. BACKATYA , with the pace three deep, was pushed along outside foes past the five sixteenths, drifted out as the leaders separated themselves in mid stretch, corrected and finished evenly. SPITBALL , off the pace, was hustled along outside a rival mid turn, shifted three to four wide in upper stretch, edged up near the sixteenth pole then flattened out. MICE AND MEN stumbled at the break, saved ground while off the pace and lacked a rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 3 5 1/2F Turf CR: 77. Maiden Special Weight Purse 60220. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race on the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five and One half Furlongs) (Rail at 52 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CIRCLE HOME , bumped by UP FOR IT leaving the starting gate, steadied in traffic entering the turn, hugged the inner rail entering the stretch, swung to the five path approaching the sixteenth pole, closed and was up late. NINETEENAMENDMENT bumped with BEE MOUNTAIN at the starting gate, saved ground around the turn, eased outside in upper stretch, bid for the lead near the sixteenth pole and was out finished. LITTLE JOSIE WALES saved ground on the turn, angled out turning for home and rallied mildly. NEGRA GATA , near the inner rail around the turn, waited for room behind horses in mid stretch, split foes late and finished willingly. BLUE HOUR , three wide around the turn while chasing the pace, advanced to the eighth pole then weakened. UP FOR IT bumped the winner when drifting out at the break, was four wide on the turn and failed to be a factor. IN HER CUPS sped to the early lead, raced along the inner rail and gave way. GILDA'S GIRL , three wide on the turn, weakened. SCARLETT STRONG was outrun. BEE MOUNTAIN bumped with NINETEENAMENDMENT at the start and fell back.
